                <h2>Square of Ban Jelacic</h2>
                <p>Welcome to Ban Jelacic Square, the heart and soul of Zagreb! This vibrant square is a hub of activity, surrounded by charming cafes, shops, and historical landmarks. Take a leisurely stroll through the square, soak in the lively atmosphere, and don't forget to admire the impressive statue of Ban Jelacic himself. Whether you're looking to shop, relax, or simply people-watch, Ban Jelacic Square is the perfect starting point for your Zagreb adventure.</p>
            </div><div id="second">
                <h2>Cathedral</h2>
                <p>Majestically towering over the city, the Zagreb Cathedral is a true architectural marvel. Step inside this awe-inspiring sanctuary and marvel at the intricate details of the stained glass windows, ornate chapels, and the grandeur of its Gothic-style structure. Climb the bell tower for breathtaking panoramic views of the city, and if you're lucky, you might even witness a mesmerizing organ concert. As the spiritual heart of Zagreb, the Cathedral is a must-see destination for history enthusiasts, art lovers, and those seeking a moment of tranquility.</p>
            </div>
            <div id="third">
                <h2> Dolac</h2>
                <p>Prepare to be enchanted by Dolac, Zagreb's beloved open-air market. This bustling marketplace is a feast for the senses, offering a dazzling array of fresh fruits, vegetables, flowers, and local delicacies. Immerse yourself in the lively atmosphere as vendors passionately showcase their goods, and be sure to strike up a conversation to learn more about the city's culinary traditions. Whether you're a foodie seeking authentic flavors or a curious traveler looking to soak up the local culture, Dolac is a must-visit destination in Zagreb.</p>
            </div>
            <div id="fourth"><h2>Saint Marko Church</h2><p>Nestled in the charming neighborhood of Upper Town, Saint Marko Church is a true gem of Zagreb. Its iconic multi-colored tiled roof is a sight to behold, showcasing the city's coat of arms and medieval emblems. Step inside this centuries-old place of worship and admire the stunning Gothic and Romanesque architecture, as well as the beautiful frescoes adorning the walls. Take a moment to absorb the peaceful ambiance, and don't forget to capture a picture-perfect moment against the backdrop of this architectural masterpiece. Saint Marko Church is a must-visit for anyone seeking a glimpse into Zagreb's rich cultural heritage.</p></div>
